.TH TRANSLATE "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
translate \- Translator powered by Google/Bing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B translate
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,TEXT\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B translate
is a script for translating text between languages. It uses online translation services (Google Translate, Bing) to provide translations from the command line.
.PP
The script supports multiple languages and can auto-detect the source language.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B translate "Hello world"
Translate to default language
.TP
.B translate -t es "Hello"
Translate to Spanish
.TP
.B echo "Bonjour" | translate -t en
Translate from stdin to English
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/translate/settings.conf
User configuration file for translate preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 4
Network connection failed
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Uses Google/Bing translation APIs
.IP \(bu 2
Auto-detect source language
.IP \(bu 2
Supports many language pairs
